<?php

namespace Database\Seeders;

use Illuminate\Database\Seeder;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\DB;

class CneContentSeeder extends Seeder
{
    public function run(): void
    {
        DB::table('cne_contents')->updateOrInsert(
            ['section' => 'eligibility'],
            [
                'title' => 'Eligibility and Selection',
                'content' => '<p><strong>Eligibility:</strong></p><ul><li>Only recognized nursing institutions, hospitals, nursing colleges, professional nursing organizations, and healthcare institutions involved in nursing education or nursing services are eligible to apply for the conduct of a Continuing Nursing Education (CNE) programme.</li><li>The applicant institution must comply with the norms and standards prescribed by the Council from time to time.</li><li>The proposed CNE programme must be relevant to nursing education, nursing practice, nursing administration, or nursing research.</li><li>The institution must propose qualified and competent resource persons, with at least one resource person being a registered nurse.</li><li>The applicant institution must agree to adhere to all guidelines, conditions, and decisions of the Council related to the conduct of CNE programmes.</li></ul><p><strong>Selection:</strong></p><ul><li>All applications received for conducting a CNE programme shall be scrutinized by the Council for completeness, relevance, and compliance with the prescribed guidelines.</li><li>The Council shall assess the:<ul><li>Objectives of the CNE programme</li><li>Target audience and number of participants</li><li>Programme content and schedule</li><li>Qualifications and suitability of resource persons</li><li>Duration of the programme and proposed credit hours</li></ul></li><li>Credit hours and credit points shall be awarded strictly in accordance with the norms as adopted by the Council from time to time.</li><li>Based on the scrutiny, the Council may:<ul><li>Approve the CNE programme with specified credit hours/credit points, or</li><li>Seek clarification or additional information, or</li><li>Reject the application if it does not meet the prescribed criteria.</li></ul></li><li>The decision of the Council regarding the selection, approval, and allotment of credit hours/credit points shall be final and binding.</li><li>Approval of the CNE programme shall be subject to:<ul><li>Successful conduct of the programme,</li><li>Submission and acceptance of the post‑programme descriptive report with supporting documents by the organising institution.</li></ul></li></ul>',
                'created_at' => now(),
                'updated_at' => now(),
            ]
        );

        DB::table('cne_contents')->updateOrInsert(
            ['section' => 'how_to_apply'],
            [
                'title' => 'How to apply',
                'content' => '<p><strong>Procedure for Applying for Continuing Nursing Education (CNE)</strong></p><p>Any institution intending to conduct a Continuing Nursing Education (CNE) programme and seeking approval for the award of credit hours / credit points from the Council shall follow the procedure outlined below.</p><p><strong>SUBMISSION OF APPLICATION:</strong><br>The institution shall submit a formal application to the Registrar of the Council, requesting permission to conduct the CNE programme and to award credit hours/credit points. The application must contain complete and accurate details of the proposed CNE.</p><p>The application shall specifically include the following details:</p><ul><li>Title / Topic and Objectives of the CNE programme</li><li>Target audience and number of participants</li><li>Venue of the programme and name of the organising institution</li><li>Date(s) and total duration (number of days) of the programme</li><li>Name and complete details of the Organising Chairperson and Organising Secretary, including:<ul><li>Full name</li><li>Designation</li><li>Institution / Organization</li><li>Contact number</li><li>Email address</li></ul></li></ul><p><strong>DETAILS OF RESOURCE PERSONS:</strong></p><ul><li>Biodata of all proposed resource persons must be submitted along with recent passport-size photographs.</li><li>At least one of the resource persons must be a qualified nurse.</li></ul><p><strong>CERTIFICATE TEMPLATE:</strong></p><ul><li>A sample/template of the participation certificate must be submitted with the application.</li><li>The certificate shall bear the official logo of the Council (downloadable from the Council website).</li><li>Adequate space for the signature of the Registrar must be provided on the certificate.</li></ul><p><strong>PROGRAMME SCHEDULE AND REGISTRATION DETAILS:</strong></p><ul><li>A detailed programme schedule must be submitted.</li><li>Registration forms must be enclosed, clearly specifying the registration process and the registration fee, if applicable.</li></ul><p>Upon receipt of the complete application, the Council shall scrutinize all submitted documents and details. Based on the scrutiny, the Council may grant permission to conduct the CNE programme and approve the applicable credit hours / credit points.</p><p><strong>POST‑PROGRAMME SUBMISSION:</strong></p><p>After successful completion of the approved CNE programme, the organising institution must submit a descriptive report to the Council within the prescribed time period.</p><p>The report shall include:</p><ul><li>Brief background and objectives of the CNE programme</li><li>Details of sessions conducted and resource persons</li><li>Number of participants attended</li><li>Outcomes and key learnings</li><li>Any challenges faced and recommendations</li></ul><p>The report must be supported with:</p><ul><li>Relevant photographs of the programme (inauguration, sessions, participants, valedictory, etc.)</li><li>Copy of the final programme schedule</li><li>Attendance sheets</li><li>Sample of participation certificate issued</li><li>Any other relevant supporting documents as required by the Council</li></ul><p>The descriptive report, along with all supporting documents, shall be submitted within 30 days of completion of the CNE programme, both in soft copy and hard copy, as follows:</p><p><strong>Soft copy:</strong> To be emailed to &ndash; assamnursingcouncil@gmail.com<br><strong>Hard copy:</strong> To be sent by post to:<br>The Registrar,<br>Assam Nurses, Midwives and Health Visitors Council,<br>O/O Director of Health Services,<br>3rd Floor, Hengrabari,<br>Guwahati &ndash; 36.</p><p>Submission of the descriptive report and supporting documents is mandatory for final confirmation of credit hours / credit points.</p>',
                'created_at' => now(),
                'updated_at' => now(),
            ]
        );
    }
}
